Skip to main contentVersion: 0.0.4On this pageMetiz can be accessed at the following address: https://metiz.triologic.at Login‚Äã Your user data will be assigned to you by Triologic. With this information, you can login on the Metiz website. To do this, an e-mail address or a username and a matching password must be entered. If you have forgotten your user data, please get in touch with Triologic (office@triologic.at) to request a new password. There are 2 different Types of Users: Admin: An administrator can assign serial numbers to TML User: Can make settings that are important for the operation of the system. Login

Skip to main contentVersion: 0.0.4The name "Metiz" is inspired by the Greek goddess Metis, who was a Titaness associated with wisdom, prudence, and deep thought. Metis was the first wife of Zeus, the king of the gods and mother of Athena.

Skip to main contentVersion: 0.0.4In order to be able to use Metiz optimally, we recommend the use of an up-to-date web browser. Metiz was tested primarily with Chrome, Safari and Firefox. With all other web browsers, there may be deviations in the presentation and functionality. For mobile applications, we recommend devices with the Android and IOS operating system and the above-mentioned web browsers. Again, there may be deviations in presentation and functionality when used in a different software environment.

Skip to main contentVersion: 0.0.4On this pageThe current outside temperature is displayed. Enter options menu Current temperature Settings Info‚Äã Irrigation Frost Protection‚Äã In the settings, you can set the activation temperature for the automatic deflation (frost protection) of the irrigation system. This function will be deactivated at a certain hysteresis which can also be adjusted in this window. If the outside temperature is under a defined limit the freeze protection program will be activated. Then the main drainage valve opens after the irrigation cycle. If the temperature is higher than the outside temperature limit + the defined hysteresis, the function will be disabled by automatic mode. This function is active, if the irrigation valves are in automatic mode. Set minimum temperature [¬∞C] Hysteresis freeze control [¬∞C] Settings InfoIrrigation Frost Protection

Manual start button (continuous operation) [B1]: Starts irrigation for this windrow until the user switches the mode or an error occurs. Skip to main contentVersion: 0.0.4 infoMetiz is actively developed and maintained by Triologic Automation GmbH. This documentation is intended for our customers only. Metiz can be considered a type of SCADA (Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition) system. SCADA systems are used for monitoring and controlling industrial processes, and Metiz fits this description as it allows users to monitor and control environmental parameters such as temperature, aeration, and irrigation in composting systems. This documentation will describe the fundamentals of using the Metiz system. This includes the widgets displayed on the facility pages as well as core components.

Zum Hauptinhalt springenVersion: 0.0.4 infoMetiz is actively developed and maintained by Triologic Automation GmbH. This documentation is intended for our customers only. Metiz can be considered a type of SCADA (Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition) system. SCADA systems are used for monitoring and controlling industrial processes, and Metiz fits this description as it allows users to monitor and control environmental parameters such as temperature, aeration, and irrigation in composting systems. This documentation will describe the fundamentals of using the Metiz system. This includes the widgets displayed on the facility pages as well as core components.

Enter options menu Current temperature Settings Info‚Äã Irrigation Frost Protection‚Äã In the settings, you can set the activation temperature for the automatic deflation (frost protection) of the irrigation system. This function will be deactivated at a certain hysteresis which can also be adjusted in this window. If the outside temperature is under a defined limit the freeze protection program will be activated. Then the main drainage valve opens after the irrigation cycle. If the temperature is higher than the outside temperature limit + the defined hysteresis, the function will be disabled by automatic mode. This function is active, if the irrigation valves are in automatic mode. Set minimum temperature [¬∞C] Hysteresis freeze control [¬∞C] Settings InfoIrrigation Frost Protection

Enter options menu Current temperature Settings Info‚Äã Irrigation Frost Protection‚Äã In the settings, you can set the activation temperature for the automatic deflation (frost protection) of the irrigation system. This function will be deactivated at a certain hysteresis which can also be adjusted in this window. If the outside temperature is under a defined limit the freeze protection program will be activated. Then the main drainage valve opens after the irrigation cycle. If the temperature is higher than the outside temperature limit + the defined hysteresis, the function will be disabled by automatic mode. This function is active, if the irrigation valves are in automatic mode. Set minimum temperature [¬∞C] Hysteresis freeze control [¬∞C] Settings InfoIrrigation Frost Protection

Przejd≈∫ do g≈Ç√≥wnej zawarto≈õciWersja: 0.0.4 informacjaMetiz is actively developed and maintained by Triologic Automation GmbH. This documentation is intended for our customers only. Metiz can be considered a type of SCADA (Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition) system. SCADA systems are used for monitoring and controlling industrial processes, and Metiz fits this description as it allows users to monitor and control environmental parameters such as temperature, aeration, and irrigation in composting systems. This documentation will describe the fundamentals of using the Metiz system. This includes the widgets displayed on the facility pages as well as core components.
